org.jscsi.target.scsi.cdb

Class ReadOrWriteCdb

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jscsi.target.scsi.cdb.CommandDescriptorBlock
      • org.jscsi.target.scsi.cdb.ReadOrWriteCdb
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ReadCdb, WriteCdb

    public abstract class ReadOrWriteCdb
extends CommandDescriptorBlock
    This abstract class represents Command Descriptor Blocks for the READ and WRITE SCSI commands. This grouping makes sense, since, apart from the different values of the OPERATION CODE field, Read and Write CDBs are identical.
    Author:
    Andreas Ergenzinger

      • addIllegalFieldPointerForLogicalBlockAddress

        public final void addIllegalFieldPointerForLogicalBlockAddress()
        This method is used for signaling an illegal value of the logicalBlockAddress variable.

        This method must be called if the logicalBlockAddress lies outside the bounds of the used medium.

        See Also:
        CommandDescriptorBlock.getIllegalFieldPointers(), IStorageModule.checkBounds(long, int)

      • addIllegalFieldPointerForTransferLength

        public final void addIllegalFieldPointerForTransferLength()
        This method is used for signaling an illegal value of the transferLength variable.

        This method must be called if the transferLength field value would result in accessing of out-of-bounds blocks of the storage medium.

        See Also:
        CommandDescriptorBlock.getIllegalFieldPointers(), IStorageModule.checkBounds(long, int)
